                     <hi rend="smallCaps">CHARLES PHILLIPS</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted<rs id="t18430508-1677-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430508-1677-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430508-1677-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18430508-cd-256" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430508-1677-offence-1 t18430508-cd-256"></join>18th of April</rs>, 1 handkerchief, value 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., the goods of a man unknown, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1437" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1437" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1437" type="surname" value="M'LOCHLAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1437" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES M'LOCHLAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable C</hi> 125.) I was in Greenwich-park, on the 18th of April, between five and six o'clock in the evening—I saw the prisoners there together—I saw Phillips take this handkerchief from gen<lb></lb>tleman's pocket, and pass it to Jones—I do not know who the gentleman was—he was in the crowd—I took Jones, and found this handkerchief in his pocket—Phillips escaped.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did Jones claim the handkerchief? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—we could not get Phillips, as the mob was so great—the gentleman was standing looking at a party playingat kiss-in-the-ring—I was in plain clothes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Phillips.</hi> You let us get away from the crowd. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, I took Jones directly.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1438" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1438" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1438" type="surname" value="BURRIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1438" type="given" value="JAMES WILLIAM"></interp>JAMES WILLIAM BURRIDGE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 160.) I was in the Park</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184305080186"></xptr>
               <p>in plain clothes—I saw Phillips take this handkerchief from a gentleman, and hand it to Jones—I pursued Phillips, but he got out of the Park—I found Phillips in Gravel-lane, in the Borough.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Who was the gentleman this handkerchief belonged to? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> That I cannot say.</p>
               <p>(Jones received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">JONES</hi>—
